Name: alpha-Terpineol
Description: Alpha-terpineol is a terpineol that is propan-2-ol substituted by a 4-methylcyclohex-3-en-1-yl group at position 2. It has a role as a plant metabolite.

plant_concentrations.References: (1) Koukos PK et al; J Agric Food Chem 48: 1266-8 (2000) (2) Schlotzhauer WS et al; J Agric Food Chem 44: 206-9 (1996) (3) VanThanh B et al; Chem Cent J 8: 54 (2014) (4) Satyal P et al; Pharmacognosy Res 5: 43-8 (2013)
plant_concentrations.Value: alpha-Terpineol was detected in oil extracted from twigs collected from the Balkan pine in Northern Greece at 0.11% of the total composition(1). Flowers freshly collected from honeysuckle plants (Lonicera japonica) contained alpha-terpineol at 81 ug/kg; honeysuckle flowers which had been open for 24 hours prior to collection contained alpha-terpineol at 102 ug/kg(2). alpha-Terpineol was detected in the essential oil of Hedychium (H.) stenopetalum (root 3.7%), H. coronarium (leaf 8.6%, root 0.1%), H. flavum (leaf 0.3%) and H. ellipticum (leaf 5.1%); all samples were collected Aug-Sept 2011 in various locations in Vietnam(3). alpha-Terpineol was detected in the essential oil from needle, bark and cone of Pinus roxburghii at 5.0, 4.0 and 2.8%, respectively; samples were collected May 13, 2011 from Biratnagar, Nepal(4).

plant_concentrations.References: (1) USDA; Dr. Duke's Phytochemical and Ethnobotanical Databases. Plants with a chosen chemical. alpha-terpineol. Washington, DC: US Dept Agric, Agric Res Service. Available from, as of June 29, 2015: https://www.ars-grin.gov/duke/
